The paper deals with the computation of functions using a combinatorial framework for procedural programming languages, which suggests that it could belong to the categories of data structures (cs.DS) or computational complexity (cs.CC). The focus on updating one variable at a time and the use of memoryless computation suggests that it could also belong to the category of programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the exact number of instructions required to compute manipulations of variables, which could fall under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO) or information theory (cs.IT).
